Ken Broskey, 69, of Livonia, Michigan, has stage 4 cancer, and has taken a job as an Uber driver .
This so he can make enough money to pay off his mortgage so his daughter and grandchildren can continue to live in his house .
Instead of checking into the hospital, Broskey has decided not to check into hospice care .
Now he is getting a job with Uber, hoping to raise enough money for his family to have his house built .